	   <tr><td colspan=2>You have misunderstood the point. We are not only jack of all trades.<br><br>We are kings and queens of stacking!.<br><br>I have not heard one time in my entire life as a bard that someone would rather have something else even when grouped with another bard.<br><br>And what you will never see is. <br><br>Do yourself a few favors.<br><br>1. Learn how to twist. 2 songs by level 10 3 songs by level 20. 4 songs if you want to but no one espects that.<br><br>2. Look at the group you are in. What classes are missed. If any fill out that class/classes.<br><br>3. Look at the monsters fought. Choose your tunes after group combination and monsters fought.<br><br>4. Stay active. Melee with your instruments or weapons while twisting.<br><br>5. Learn how to handle agro.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Cyrix<br>60 Bard<br>Test</td></tr>
